Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{} on to boil for the potato. Trim
the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then slice
widthways. Trim the @green beans{150%g}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks
(no need to peel). Add to the pan of boiling water and cook until you can easily slip
a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, return to
the pan (off the heat) and cover with a lid.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the leek
with a pinch of @salt{}. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}, then transfer to a #plate{}.
Season the @British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Put another splash
of @oil{} in your frying pan. Add the chicken and cook until the outside is brown and
the inside cooked through, ~{8%minutes} each side.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When your chicken is cooked, add the @creme fraiche{75%g} to the pan along with the
@cider & horseradish wholegrain mustard{1/2%tsp}, leek and a splash of @water{}. Stir and
cook for another ~{3%minutes} until everything is combined and hot. Spoon a little
of the creamy sauce over your chicken and set the pan aside, covering the pan with
a lid or some #foil{} to keep your chicken warm.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in another frying pan on medium heat. Add the
@mustard seeds{1/2%tsp} and cook for ~{30%seconds}. Add the green beans along with
a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until slightly softened, ~{3%minutes}, then
add a splash of @water{} to the pan, cover with a lid or some foil and cook for
~{4%minutes} more.

Next, add a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} to the drained potato in your pan, along
with a knob of @?butter{} (if you have some) and a splash of @?milk{} (if you have
any). Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and keep warm with the lid on.

When everything is ready, stir a splash of hot water into the sauce, if the liquid has
evaporated too much. Take the chicken out of the pan and slice into 2cm slices. Serve
your chicken with the mash, your stir-fried green beans and a good helping of the
creamy mustard sauce. Enjoy!

> Look at what you have made! Feeling proud? You should be. Take a moment to enjoy
> this moment, you deserve it.